						<p>The fragmentary inscription seems to mention a gift of paddy for bathing ceremony <hi rend="italic">(snapanam)</hi> in the temple of Tiruvirumbūdaluḍaiya Mahādēva by the assembly of Manukulachūḷāmaṇi-chaturvēdimaṅgalam.</p>						

